# Fallout Mockery — Project Rules

- TypeScript only in `src/`. No new `.js` game logic files.
- Use `@/` path alias for imports.
- Game logic mutates `GameState` through systems in `src/systems/`.
- Rendering code in `src/render/` must not mutate combat or movement state.
- Prefer typed interfaces from `src/core/types.ts` over inline object shapes.
- Do not add `global`, `window.game`, or god-object context blobs.
- Keep modules small and single-purpose; split files over ~200 lines when adding features.
